cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Performance Evaluation Across Implementations and Bandwidth Conditions
abstract: This dataset captures performance metrics of multiple QUIC protocol implementations
  under varying bandwidth constraints. The experiment measures transfer reliability,
  energy consumption, latency, and cryptographic handshake efficiency through synchronized
  client-server workflows. Repeated trials with different configurations generate
  logs, checksums, and timing data for statistical analysis. Evaluation scripts aggregate
  results to compare goodput, transfer time, and success rates, producing visualizations
  and TSV files for implementation comparison.
